    "body": "## Problem\n\nTake the following annotation from a definition file:\n\n```lua\n---Configures the font to use by default.\n---\n---The font setting can specify a set of fallbacks and other options,\n---and is described in more detail in the [Fonts section](https://wezterm.org/config/fonts.html).\n---\n---You will typically use [`wezterm.font`](lua://Wezterm.font) or\n---[`wezterm.font_with_fallback`](lua://Wezterm.font_with_fallback) to specify the font.\n---\n---@field font? AllFontAttributes\n```\n\nThe hyperlink is a valid one for LuaLS (see [_Referring to Symbols_](https://luals.github.io/wiki/annotations/#referring-to-symbols) in LuaLS Wiki).\nHowever, when running `vim.lsp.buf.hover()` on that function, the rendering gets mangled:\n\n<img width=\"1088\" height=\"362\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84dd3702-a163-44b9-b768-81b80237905e\" />\n\n## Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n### Minimal Config\n\n**_The issue happens either way._**\n\n<details>\n<summary><code>minimal_init.lua</code></summary>\n\nSome config was pulled from the `lua_ls` section in `:h lspconfig-all`.\n\n```lua\n--- CHANGE THESE\nlocal pattern = 'lua'\nlocal cmd = { 'lua-language-server' }\n-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project\nlocal root_markers = {\n    '.luarc.json',\n    '.luarc.jsonc',\n    '.luacheckrc',\n    '.stylua.toml',\n    'stylua.toml',\n    'selene.toml',\n    'selene.yml',\n    '.git',\n}\n-- Change to table with settings if required\nlocal settings = {\n    Lua = {\n        addonManager = { enable = true },\n        codeLens = { enable = true },\n        completion = {\n            autoRequire = false,\n            callSnippet = 'Replace',\n            displayContext = 8,\n            enable = true,\n            keywordSnippet = 'Replace',\n            postfix = '@',\n            requireSeparator = '.',\n            showParams = true,\n            showWord = 'Enable',\n            workspaceWord = true,\n        },\n        diagnostics = { enable = true },\n        format = {\n            defaultConfig = {\n                indent_size = 4,\n                indent_style = 'space',\n            },\n            enable = true,\n        },\n        hint = {\n            arrayIndex = 'Auto',\n            await = true,\n            enable = true,\n            paramName = 'All',\n            paramType = true,\n            semicolon = 'SameLine',\n            setType = true,\n        },\n        hover = {\n            enable = true,\n            enumsLimit = 50,\n            expandAlias = true,\n            previewFields = 50,\n            viewNumber = true,\n            viewString = true,\n            viewStringMax = 1000,\n        },\n        runtime = {\n            fileEncoding = 'utf8',\n            path = { '?.lua', 'lua/?.lua', 'lua/?/init.lua' },\n            pathStrict = false,\n            unicodeName = false,\n        },\n        semantic = { annotation = true, enable = true, keyword = true, variable = true },\n        signatureHelp = { enable = true },\n        type = {\n            castNumberToInteger = false,\n            inferParamType = true,\n            weakNilCheck = true,\n            weakUnionCheck = true,\n        },\n        window = { progressBar = false, statusBar = false },\n        workspace = { checkThirdParty = false, useGitIgnore = true },\n    },\n}\n\nvim.lsp.log.set_level(vim.log.levels.DEBUG)\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\n    pattern = pattern,\n    callback = function(args)\n        local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\n        local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil\n        vim.lsp.start({\n            name = 'lua_ls',\n            cmd = cmd,\n            root_dir = root_dir,\n            settings = settings,\n        })\n\n        vim.keymap.set('n', 'K', vim.lsp.buf.hover, {\n            noremap = true,\n            silent = true,\n            buffer = args.buf,\n        })\n    end,\n})\n```\n\n</details>\n\n### Folder Layout\n\nIf I understood correctly, the folder layout can be found in [DrKJeff16/wezterm-types](https://github.com/DrKJeff16/wezterm-types).\n\n### How To Cause\n\n1. Map `vim.lsp.buf.hover()` to a keymap, like so:\n  ```lua\n  vim.keymap.set('n', 'K', vim.lsp.buf.hover, { ... })\n  ```\n2. Press `K` on identifier with annotation containing a `[...](lua://...)` comment\n3. Hover is broken :(\n\n---\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nFor the hover to render properly like normal Markdown hyperlinks do:\n\n```lua\n---Configures the font to use by default.\n---\n---The font setting can specify a set of fallbacks and other options,\n---and is described in more detail in the [Fonts section](https://wezterm.org/config/fonts.html).\n---\n---You will typically use [`wezterm.font`](https://wezterm.org/config/lua/wezterm/font.html) or\n---[`wezterm.font_with_fallback`](https://wezterm.org/config/lua/wezterm/font_with_fallback.html) to specify the font.\n---\n---@field font? AllFontAttributes\n```\n\n<img width=\"1117\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0cb624c8-3387-48c9-a624-288323ecaa34\" />\n\n---\n\n## Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1064+g29c5559ce1\n\n## Language server name/version\n\nLuaLS 3.15.0.r23.g24b9faa66-1 (ArchLinux AUR Build)\n\n## Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux (Linux 6.16.2-zen1-1-zen)\n\n## Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/DrKJeff16/633c5ded1d37900bf540036a583292a8",
