            "body": "> I stared at the screenshots, which btw are showing different contents, and don't get what you mean by \"mangled\".\n\n@justinmk Sorry, English is not my mother tongue so I wasn't sure about what word to use.\n\nIn a more precise manner, I hope, it looks like `[...](lua://...)` hyperlinks don't render the same way as normal ones (`[...](https://...)`) do. It looks like the former gets wrapped around like normal text... or at least that's my conjecture as a first impression.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison\n\nHere I'm using the same annotation in two separate cases.\nI've only edited the URI fields, nothing else.\n\nThe full context of these annotations can be found [here](https://github.com/DrKJeff16/wezterm-types/blob/main/lua/wezterm/types/config.lua#L929).\n\n<details>\n<summary><ins>Using</ins> <code>lua://</code> <ins>hyperlinks</ins></summary>\n\n```lua\n---Configures the font to use by default.\n---\n---The font setting can specify a set of fallbacks and other options,\n---and is described in more detail in the [Fonts section](https://wezterm.org/config/fonts.html).\n---\n---You will typically use [`wezterm.font`](lua://Wezterm.font) or\n---[`wezterm.font_with_fallback`](lua://Wezterm.font_with_fallback) to specify the font.\n---\n---@field font? AllFontAttributes\n```\n\n<img width=\"1088\" height=\"362\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84dd3702-a163-44b9-b768-81b80237905e\" />\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><ins>Using</ins> <code>https://</code> <ins>hyperlinks</ins></summary>\n\n```lua\n---Configures the font to use by default.\n---\n---The font setting can specify a set of fallbacks and other options,\n---and is described in more detail in the [Fonts section](https://wezterm.org/config/fonts.html).\n---\n---You will typically use [`wezterm.font`](https://wezterm.org/config/lua/wezterm/font.html) or\n---[`wezterm.font_with_fallback`](https://wezterm.org/config/lua/wezterm/font_with_fallback.html) to specify the font.\n---\n---@field font? AllFontAttributes\n```\n\n<img width=\"1117\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0cb624c8-3387-48c9-a624-288323ecaa34\" />\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\nHope this explanation is more useful. Sorry for the confusion.",
