        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This happens because a lua:// expands into a long file:// URI that exceeds the available screen width. You can confirm this by zooming in or by inserting any arbitrarily long string inside `()`. This behavior is not specific to hyperlinks - it is simply how wrapping works for concealed text.\n\nA possible improvement would be to account for concealed text only when it is actually visible. This would both avoid unnecessary wrapping and allow floating windows to use less width. In some cases, the concealed text is actually the widest part of the message, which results in floating windows being created with more width than needed. For example, in gopls, where a documentation link is added to each hover.\n\n<img width=\"2378\" height=\"318\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f10e9b2-783e-4046-b7c3-1869974d5d35\" />\n\nThis is just a rough idea - I am not sure how feasible it would be to implement, or how it should coexist with the current wrapping behavior.",
